Internship Agreement (High-Risk / Internally
Inconsistent Sample)
This Internship Agreement (this “Agreement”) is entered into on [EFFECTIVE DATE] by and
between [COMPANY NAME], a company organized under the laws of [STATE/COUNTRY],
with its principal office at [COMPANY ADDRESS] (the “Company”), and [INTERN NAME],
residing at [INTERN ADDRESS] (the “Intern”).
1. Term; Position; Reporting
1.1 The Intern will serve as “Intern” in the [DEPARTMENT] department beginning on
[START DATE] and continuing until [END DATE], unless earlier terminated under this
Agreement.
1.2 The Intern will report to [SUPERVISOR NAME] and will perform tasks assigned by the
Company from time to time.
2. Working Time; Attendance; Control
2.1 The Intern will work full-time hours of not less than 45 hours per week (and as many
additional hours as required to meet business needs), including weekends if directed by
the Company.
2.2 The Company will control the manner, method, timing, and location of the Intern’s
work. The Intern will comply with all Company directions and policies.
3. Compensation; Taxes; Benefits
3.1 The Internship is unpaid. The Intern acknowledges that no wages, stipend, or other
compensation is owed for any work performed under this Agreement.
3.2 Notwithstanding Section 3.1, the Intern will be eligible for Company employee benefits
and perks that the Company makes available from time to time, in the Company’s sole
discretion.
3.3 The Intern is solely responsible for all taxes and statutory payments, if any, arising
from this Internship.
4. Employment Status (Conflicting Statement)
4.1 The Intern is not an employee of the Company and will not be entitled to any
employee rights, protections, or benefits.
4.2 The Intern agrees that the Internship is equivalent to full-time employment for
purposes of duties, performance expectations, and Company control.
5. Confidentiality (Overbroad)
5.1 “Confidential Information” means any information that the Company considers
confidential, whether or not marked confidential, including information the Intern learns in
meetings, hallway conversations, or by observation.
5.2 The Intern will keep all Confidential Information strictly confidential forever and will not
disclose it to any person for any reason, including to comply with a court order or law.
5.3 The Intern will not use Confidential Information for any purpose other than the
Company’s benefit, including after the Internship ends.
6. Intellectual Property (Overreaching Assignment)
6.1 The Intern hereby irrevocably assigns to the Company all rights, title, and interest in
and to any and all ideas, inventions, discoveries, designs, works of authorship, code,
improvements, processes, trade secrets, and other intellectual property, whether or not
patentable or copyrightable (collectively, “Works”), that the Intern creates, conceives, or
reduces to practice at any time during the term of this Agreement.
6.2 The assignment in Section 6.1 includes Works created (a) on the Intern’s own time, (b)
without use of Company equipment, (c) outside the scope of the Internship, and (d) even if
unrelated to the Company’s business.
6.3 The Intern waives all moral rights and similar rights worldwide in all Works, whether
now known or later recognized.
7. Non-Compete (Post-Termination Restriction)
7.1 During the Internship and for a period of two (2) years after the Internship ends, the
Intern will not, directly or indirectly, anywhere in India or any other country, (a) work for,
consult for, or provide services to any person or entity that competes with the Company,
or (b) start, invest in, or assist any competing business.
7.2 The Intern agrees that this restriction is reasonable and necessary and that the Intern
has had adequate opportunity to obtain legal advice.
8. Non-Solicitation (Broad)
8.1 For two (2) years after the Internship ends, the Intern will not solicit, induce, or
encourage any employee, intern, contractor, customer, supplier, or prospective customer
of the Company to end or reduce its relationship with the Company.
9. Device Use; Monitoring
9.1 The Intern will use personal devices for Company work as required. The Company may
monitor all communications and access all data on any device used for Company work,
including personal messages and files, at any time without notice.
10. Indemnity (One-Sided)
10.1 The Intern will indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Company and its affiliates
from and against any and all claims, demands, losses, liabilities, damages, penalties,
costs, and expenses (including attorneys’ fees) arising out of or relating to (a) the
Internship, (b) any act or omission of the Intern, or (c) any allegation that the Intern should
have been treated as an employee.
11. Termination
11.1 The Company may terminate this Agreement at any time, with or without cause,
without notice.
11.2 The Intern may not terminate this Agreement before the end date. If the Intern stops
working early, the Intern will pay the Company liquidated damages of INR [AMOUNT] plus
all Company costs associated with recruiting a replacement.
12. Dispute Resolution; Venue
12.1 Any dispute arising out of or relating to this Agreement will be submitted exclusively
to the courts located in [FOREIGN VENUE/CITY], and the Intern irrevocably consents to
such jurisdiction.
12.2 The Company may seek injunctive relief in any court worldwide.
13. Governing Law
This Agreement will be governed by the laws of [FOREIGN LAW/JURISDICTION], without
regard to conflicts of laws principles.
14. Entire Agreement; Changes
14.1 This Agreement is the entire agreement and supersedes all prior understandings.
14.2 The Company may amend this Agreement at any time by posting an updated version
on its internal portal, and the Intern will be deemed to have accepted the amendment by
continuing the Internship.
15. Signatures
The parties have executed this Agreement as of the Effective Date.
